[normal]The Big Lottery Fund (the Fund) is the largest Lottery distributor, responsible for distributing 40% of funds raised for ‘good causes’ from The National Lottery. Since June 2004, we have awarded over £6bn to projects supporting health, education, environme
[normal]nt and charitable purposes. In 2012/2013 
[normal]92% of our funding went directly to the 
[normal]voluntary,
[normal] community sector 
[normal]and
[normal] social enterprise
