[normal]&#xa0;[bold]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In June 2012 the Fund launched 
[normal]Talent Match (England)[bold],
[normal] a major new £100 million investment that seeks to support young people aged 18 - 24 in England who are 
[normal]furthest from the labour market (
[normal]e
[normal].
[normal]g
[normal]. those 
[normal]who have been out of work, education or training for over 12 months
[normal], or those who are completely disengaged from benefits and other systems
[normal])
[normal]. 
[normal]Big Lottery funding will be used to
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]create pathways for young people
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]employers 
[normal]and other organisations 
[normal]to come together and help young people find work or set up their own enterprises. 
[normal]Talent Match goes beyond simply improving the employability of young people, intending to address barriers to work and achieve sustainable, 
[normal]meaningful employment for a significant number of those engaged.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Of relevance to Question 6[bold]: 
[normal]T
[normal]he Fund 
[normal]co-designed this investment with  a team of
[normal] young people aged 16-25
[normal] and worked with
[normal] a 
[normal]range
[normal] of experts 
[normal]to determine
[normal] how Lottery funding might best make a positive contribution. 
[normal] Young p
[normal]eople also acted as full Committee members alongside the Fund’s Committee making decisions on Talent Match applications.  
[normal]A
[normal] video and a podcast illustrate why the young people got involved in our investment and why it is so important to involve young people in decisions of this kind. These can be viewed at the Fund’s website at 
[normal]http://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/global-content/programmes/england/talent-match
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We have used evidence 
[normal]on areas such as unemployment levels and employment opportunities 
[normal]to target 21
[normal] areas across England wher
[normal]e we will seek to 
[normal]achieve a significant and lasting impact. 
[normal]We ha
[normal]ve taken a range of considerations and the advice of stakeholders and young people into account when deciding where to target, and chosen the geographic areas covered by Local Enterprise Part
[normal]nerships (LEP) as our start point
[normal], these areas reflecting economic rather than traditional boundaries
[normal]. In each of these areas partnerships have been formed to bring about locally owned solutions to local youth unemployment issues and to 
[normal]use their local int
[normal]elligence and experience to 
[normal]further refine our chosen areas.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Each 
[normal]of the 21 target areas 
[normal]will receive 
[normal]a 
[normal]grant
[normal] of
[normal] between £1 million and £10 million for a portfolio of activities lasting up to five years. All partnerships are led by a VCSE organisation wit
[normal]h experience of working with young people who are not in work, education or training and include representatives from local businesses, employers, education and training providers and local authorities. For details of the 21 target areas and contact inform
[normal]ation for each partnership lead, see 
[normal]http://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/global-content/programmes/england/talent-match
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]Big Lottery Fund is offering LEPs the 
[normal]opportunity to ’opt-in’
[normal] with us for
[normal] a single delivery and match-funding service 
[normal]through
[normal] the
[normal]ir
[normal] 2014-2020 European Structural and Investment Fund
[normal] strategies. Our offer aligns to the social inclusion and poverty objective. Over the coming months, we will be w
[normal]orking closely with those LEPs that decide to op-in to understand their local needs and refine the delivery arrangements. From conversations already in train, we expect that out learning, expertise and networks from Talent Match will be of considerable int
[normal]erest to LEPs, and a strong element of many of their strategies. We will work to 
[normal]share
[normal] learning across our work involving European funding in England. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Talent Match will involve a significant economic evaluation, which will seek to inform commissioners of
[normal] future services aimed at supporting young people into employment, and will share learning and facilitate networking from projects as they begin to roll out. 
