[normal]2.10
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]Getting Ahead (Wales)[bold] programme is a £3.4 million investment
[normal], which
[normal] 
[normal]seeks to engage, prepare and motivate young people aged 16–18 years into undertaking a six month paid supported work placement in order to enhance their chances of progress
[normal]ing into sustainable employment or further learning or training by increasing their employability skills. It will target young people aged 16-18 who have offended and young people who are leaving care. The programme is 
[normal]funded by money from dormant bank accounts. 
[normal]How to spend this money 
[normal]was
[normal] been decided by the Welsh Government and the Fund has worked closely with the Welsh Government to develop this programme. 
[normal]http://www.bigfund.org.uk/global-content/programmes/wales/gett
[normal]i
[normal]ng-ahead
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.11
