[normal]Life Skills[bold] 
[normal](Wales) [bold]programme is jointly funded with the Welsh European Funding Office, and matches Lottery funding with European Structural Funds. The p
[normal]rogramme enables care leavers, carers and former carers
[normal] and
[normal] eco
[normal]nomically inactive families 
[normal]to develop their life skills, increase their confidence, and reengage and continue to access education, learning, volunteering or employment. Four contracts worth £2
[normal].4 million were awarded in 2011/12 following a competitive procurement process. 
